# spec.tasks — PitchTwin

## Task Breakdown by Phase

---

### PHASE 0 — Project Setup
- [x] T-001: Create directory structure (`agents/`, `templates/`, `static/`, `data/`, `spec/`, `tests/`)
- [x] T-002: Write `spec.plan`
- [x] T-003: Write `spec.tasks`
- [x] T-004: Write `spec.arch`
- [ ] T-005: Write `requirements.txt`
- [ ] T-006: Write `Dockerfile` + `docker-compose.yml`
- [ ] T-007: Write `.env.example`

---

### PHASE 1 — Data Layer
- [ ] T-101: Implement `db.py` — SQLite init, schema creation
- [ ] T-102: Implement `models.py` — ConsultantProfile, Proposal, TwinSession dataclasses
- [ ] T-103: Add JSON seed data for demo consultant profile (`data/sample_profile.json`)
- [ ] T-104: Add JSON seed data for demo client brief (`data/sample_brief.json`)

---

### PHASE 2 — LLM Client
- [ ] T-201: Implement `llm_client.py` — wrapper for Gemini API (primary) and Groq (fallback)
- [ ] T-202: Add `call_llm(system_prompt, user_message)` function
- [ ] T-203: Add retry logic (3 attempts, exponential backoff)
- [ ] T-204: Add `.env` config loading (API keys)

---

### PHASE 3 — Agents
- [ ] T-301: Implement `agents/profile_agent.py` — parse raw profile → structured JSON
- [ ] T-302: Implement `agents/client_research_agent.py` — brief + company → context JSON
- [ ] T-303: Implement `agents/matching_agent.py` — profile + context → relevance map
- [ ] T-304: Implement `agents/writer_agent.py` — relevance map → CV, bio, talking points
- [ ] T-305: Implement `agents/gap_agent.py` — requirements + profile → gap analysis
- [ ] T-306: Implement `agents/persona_agent.py` — profile + matches → chat response function
- [ ] T-307: Implement `agents/debrief_agent.py` — transcript → debrief report

---

### PHASE 4 — Orchestrator
- [ ] T-401: Implement `orchestrator.py` — `run_proposal_pipeline(consultant_id, brief, company)`
- [ ] T-402: Run Profile Agent + Client Research Agent in parallel (threading)
- [ ] T-403: Chain Matching → Writer → Gap sequentially after parallel phase
- [ ] T-404: Store all outputs to SQLite
- [ ] T-405: Return proposal object with all artifacts

---

### PHASE 5 — Flask App
- [ ] T-501: Implement `app.py` — Flask app factory, route registration
- [ ] T-502: Route `GET /` — consultant dashboard (list proposals)
- [ ] T-503: Route `POST /proposal/new` — trigger pipeline, return proposal ID
- [ ] T-504: Route `GET /proposal/<id>` — view proposal package
- [ ] T-505: Route `GET /twin/<session_id>` — client twin chat interface
- [ ] T-506: Route `POST /twin/<session_id>/message` — send message, get twin response
- [ ] T-507: Route `POST /twin/<session_id>/end` — end session, trigger debrief
- [ ] T-508: Route `GET /debrief/<proposal_id>` — view debrief report

---

### PHASE 6 — Frontend Templates
- [ ] T-601: `templates/base.html` — shared layout, minimal CSS
- [ ] T-602: `templates/dashboard.html` — list proposals, trigger new proposal form
- [ ] T-603: `templates/proposal.html` — display CV, bio, talking points, gap analysis
- [ ] T-604: `templates/twin_chat.html` — client-facing chat UI (polling-based)
- [ ] T-605: `templates/debrief.html` — consultant debrief view
- [ ] T-606: `static/css/style.css` — clean minimal styling

---

### PHASE 7 — Integration & Demo
- [ ] T-701: Wire seed data to demo flow (one-click demo trigger)
